d non-Germans. The image of the Sinti and Roma prevalent in German society and literature is one similarly founded on misconceptions and stereotypes. This volume deals in depth with the life of the Sinti and Roma in Germany and their representation in German literature, giving the background to the maltreatment, underlining the fact that the persecution of Gypsies during the Nazi period, which until the 1980s has been totally marginalized by historians, did not cease in 1945. The continuity of anti-Gypsyism is traced to the present day, and the efforts, achievements and aspirations of the Sinti and Roma civil rights movement are highlighted.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 04. Okt 2022) 0aGerman literaturexHistory and criticism. 0aRomanies in literature. 0aRomanieszGermany. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Ethnic Studies / General.2bisacsh1 aEiber, Ludwig, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGrant, Anthony P., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKrausnick, Michail, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMatras, Yaron, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMilton, Sybil, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSolms, Wilhelm, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStrauß, Daniel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTebbutt, Susan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTebbutt, Susan, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBerghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311099828340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978178238187740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781782381877423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/978178